Package populationModel

Class ConfigurableSimulation

java.lang.Object
populationModel.ConfigurableSimulation
public class ConfigurableSimulation
extends java.lang.Object
A wrapper for simulation which e.g. may be used in a matlab environment. It allows to step through the tiemsteps and change parameters

      public ConfigurableSimulation​(java.lang.String inputFile) throws java.io.IOException
      generate a fresh simulation

  • Method Details

    • step

      public int[] step()
      perform one step of the simulation with current parameters repeats cyclically (with t=1) when more than @code duration steps have been performed
      Returns:
      array of population statistics. Semantics of the positions can be found with the static IDX_* methods

    • step

      public int[] step​(int k)
      like step() but computes multiple steps at once and
      Parameters:
      k - number of steps
      Returns:
      array of population statistics after k steps

    • resetAll

      public void resetAll​(double[] params)
      Change the simulation's parameters using a vector of length 10 in the following order:
      1. muBirth = [muBirth, slopeBirthrate]
      2. muDeathF
      3. muDeathM
      4. lambdaImmi
      5. muEmi
      Parameters:
      params - a vector

    • resetInitialPopulation

      public void resetInitialPopulation​(int sizeF, int sizeM)
      Change the initial population size
      Parameters:
      sizeF - number of female inhabitants
      sizeM - number of male inhabitants

    • resetDuration

      public void resetDuration​(int duration)
      set number of consecutive time steps the simulation models. Only possible at the end of a simulation.
      Parameters:
      duration - changed simulation duration

    • getCurrentSettings

      public java.lang.String getCurrentSettings()
      A simulation is mostly defined by all it's rates
      Returns:
      A very long string with all of the parameters rates (and slopes)
